<font color="#FF0000">PTSD = WHAT?</font><br>
<tt>Sun Sep 21  3:08:29 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Doc Spatz:  for the most part I concur with your statements regarding PTSD.. but not all of it.  <br>
You say that Cook &quot;clearly does not have PTSD.&quot;  I believe that you and I do not have enough data to make a statement like that.  I find it hard to believe that anyone who has exposed himself to the challenges that Cook has faced is totally free of PTSD...more likely someone like Cook would be a prime candidate for PTSD at some level.<br>
Cookie, if you're reading... I'm not saying that you do or do not have PTSD.  I would like to say &quot;people who have experienced what you have experienced... instead of throwing your name around like a public ball.&quot;<br>
I feel that both Cook and SW are not only men of great values but are highly intelligent.. and well indoctrinated.<br>
Men of this type are more adept at using defense mechanisms ... those psychic stratagems that reduce anxiety (fear) by concealing the finite source of anxiety from the self and the world.<br>
For years I could not address the fact that I had killed many children.. later I could skim over the realization that I had killed many Vietnamese children... Finally, with much pain I delved into the horror of the actual events in great detail and admitted to myself (self) that I had been stepping over the dirt that I had swept under the rug... a source of my psychic pain was recognized by ME... the treatment began at that point and continues.<br>
Without insult, I question your statement about Cook and in the same vein of respect ask for your views on Delayed PTSD.<br>
Could we be seeing a lot of Denial of Reality, Repression, Rationalization, Projection, Reaction Formation, Displacement, Emotional Insulation, Intellectualization, Regression, Overcompensation and Acting Out?<br>
Is it possible that we are seeing Affect overwhelm Cognition.. or Cognition shut down Affect.. or a flip flop between the two?<br>
I propose a thread to discuss PTSD in depth.. not the usual irate bullshit from disturbed veterans and certainly not the stale rethoric and half baked theories that evolve from the primitive disciplines of psychology, pill pushers and dumbasses who are unenlightened or uncaring.<br>
I would suggest that everything be presented in layman's terms.. and encourage the input from every person seeking an answer or an explanation.  Where we concur in numbers... strength will be gained.. where we differ, enlightenment will surface through debate and close scrutiny.<br><br>
Mustang Two Four
